WEBVTT

00:01.102 --> 00:02.735
Previously
 on Crazy Ex-Girlfriend...

00:02.770 --> 00:05.106
You love him. Say it.

00:05.139 --> 00:07.041
I just want to be his
friend, just like I want
to be all of their friends.

00:07.075 --> 00:09.043
Why don't you understand me?
(scoffs)

00:09.077 --> 00:12.313
Why did she move here again?
She was offered
a killer job in town.

00:12.346 --> 00:14.748
Why else would she move here?

00:14.782 --> 00:18.652
You called me. You said,
"I will work for super cheap.

00:18.686 --> 00:20.788
I just really want to
live in West Covina."

00:20.821 --> 00:23.624
REBECCA: Josh found out
 I've been lying, and...

00:23.657 --> 00:25.393
instead of turning his back
on me,

00:25.426 --> 00:27.228
he just opened up.
I'm so happy

00:27.261 --> 00:30.598
that you're in town, and I
don't think you're crazy at all.

00:30.631 --> 00:32.600
I love him so much.

00:32.633 --> 00:35.736
* I was working hard
at a New York job *

00:35.769 --> 00:37.605
* Making dough
but it made me blue *

00:37.638 --> 00:39.340
* One day I was crying a lot

00:39.373 --> 00:40.541
* And so I decided to move

00:40.574 --> 00:42.276
* To West Covina, California

00:42.310 --> 00:43.511
* Brand-new pals
and new career *

00:43.544 --> 00:45.513
* It happens to be
where Josh lives *

00:45.546 --> 00:48.349
* But that's not why I'm here

00:48.382 --> 00:50.484
* She's the crazy
 ex-girlfriend *
What? No, I'm not.

00:50.518 --> 00:52.220
* She's the crazy
 ex-girlfriend *

00:52.253 --> 00:53.221
That's a sexist term.

00:53.254 --> 00:54.755
* She's the crazy
 ex-girlfriend *

00:54.788 --> 00:56.090
Can you guys stop singing
for just a second?

00:56.124 --> 00:58.592
* She's so broken inside *

00:58.626 --> 01:00.228
The situation's
a lot more nuanced than that.

01:00.261 --> 01:02.263
* C-R-A-Z-Y *

01:02.296 --> 01:03.597
Okay! We get it!

01:03.631 --> 01:05.566
* Crazy ex-girlfriend. *

01:05.599 --> 01:07.435
Say it again.

01:07.468 --> 01:09.203
I love him.

01:09.237 --> 01:10.371
Say it with his name.

01:10.404 --> 01:11.505
I love Josh.

01:11.539 --> 01:12.740
Say his full name.

01:12.773 --> 01:14.742
(laughing):
Paula, I'm not...

01:15.676 --> 01:17.111
(sighs) I love...

01:17.145 --> 01:19.613
Joshua Felix Chan.

01:19.647 --> 01:21.249
(both laugh)

01:21.282 --> 01:23.517
"Mr. and Mrs. Bunch request
the honor of your presence

01:23.551 --> 01:25.253
"at the wedding
of their daughter

01:25.286 --> 01:28.756
Rebecca Nora Bunch
and Joshua Felix Chan."

01:28.789 --> 01:31.125
Paula, we're not close to
getting married, you know.

01:31.159 --> 01:34.762
It's not like I've been Googling
pictures of mixed-race babies.

01:34.795 --> 01:37.231
They're so cute-- they're so
much cuter than the plain ones.

01:37.265 --> 01:38.632
And you're not
in denial anymore,

01:38.666 --> 01:40.534
and that is the first step.
(gasps)

01:40.568 --> 01:42.770
Yay.
Yay. Okay,
so what's the plan?

01:42.803 --> 01:45.139
I have one. You break
into his apartment one night

01:45.173 --> 01:47.341
when you know Valencia is off
on one of her yoga retreats,

01:47.375 --> 01:50.444
he comes home,
you're in bed, naked.

01:50.478 --> 01:52.713
I did that at least ten times
in the '90s,

01:52.746 --> 01:55.783
and it worked every time.
He has

01:55.816 --> 01:57.418
a live-in girlfriend.

01:57.451 --> 01:59.187
I'm not gonna
just break them up.

01:59.220 --> 02:01.289
It's against my moral code.
Oh,

02:01.322 --> 02:03.391
your morals are not up to code,
honey.

02:03.424 --> 02:04.558
Hey.

02:04.592 --> 02:06.460
Sorry.
I just wish
there was some way

02:06.494 --> 02:08.461
for him to remember how it felt
when we were at camp together,

02:08.496 --> 02:12.166
you know? Every time we saw
each other, it was like...

02:12.200 --> 02:16.570
it was like Cupid's arrow went
straight through our hearts.

02:16.604 --> 02:17.738
Gotcha, Becks! (laughs)

02:17.771 --> 02:19.173
Josh!
Hey,

02:19.207 --> 02:20.474
I'll take a few of these

02:20.508 --> 02:22.610
and just ten of everything
and one boba tea to go.

02:22.643 --> 02:23.744
Wow, you're hungry.

02:23.777 --> 02:24.812
Oh, they're not for me.

02:24.845 --> 02:26.314
They're for my kids.

02:26.347 --> 02:26.947
Oh,

02:26.980 --> 02:27.848
hi.

02:27.881 --> 02:28.849
Paula.

02:28.882 --> 02:30.418
We met at Rebecca's party.

02:30.451 --> 02:32.420
Of course. Hello, ma'am.

02:32.453 --> 02:34.722
I'm not a... ma'am.
Now's not the time.

02:34.755 --> 02:35.856
What kids
are you buying candy for?

02:35.889 --> 02:37.391
Oh, it's this thing
I do every year.

02:37.425 --> 02:39.527
Um, volunteer at a program
for disadvantaged teens.

02:39.560 --> 02:41.595
Oh, my gosh,
that's so sweet.

02:41.629 --> 02:42.896
Well, I like to give back.

02:42.930 --> 02:45.366
They're a tough bunch,
but you know how kids are.

02:45.399 --> 02:47.201
You let 'em make a s'more
in the great outdoors,

02:47.235 --> 02:48.302
and their defenses just melt.

02:48.336 --> 02:50.571
S'more? W-W... Wait, s'when?

02:50.604 --> 02:52.206
S'where? With s'who? (chuckles)

02:52.240 --> 02:53.741
(laughs)
I like that. That's cute.

02:53.774 --> 02:54.742
Yeah.
Yeah, we go to Riverside

02:54.775 --> 02:56.577
and stay at this park overnight.

02:56.610 --> 02:57.745
It's just like summer camp.

02:57.778 --> 02:59.213
(echoing):
 Summer camp. Summer camp.

02:59.247 --> 03:01.349
Summer camp.

03:01.382 --> 03:02.250
PAULA:
That sounds

03:02.283 --> 03:03.751
like fun.

03:03.784 --> 03:06.487
And so romantic
for you and, uh, Valencia?

03:06.520 --> 03:08.356
Oh, she doesn't come.

03:08.389 --> 03:09.857
Actually,
she's not happy I'm going.

03:09.890 --> 03:11.359
She thinks I should be working.

03:11.392 --> 03:13.494
She has this theory
that time is money.

03:13.527 --> 03:14.795
You know who
loves camp?

03:14.828 --> 03:17.498
I mean, like, has a PhD in camp

03:17.531 --> 03:19.733
and could do a
lot for all those

03:19.767 --> 03:23.271
underprivileged...
whatever-they-ares, this one

03:23.304 --> 03:24.238
right here.

03:24.272 --> 03:26.940
Well, you know,
we're always looking for help.

03:26.974 --> 03:28.676
I'll-I'll tell them
you'll come to the office

03:28.709 --> 03:29.943
and see the camp director.

03:29.977 --> 03:31.612
Great. (chuckles)

03:31.645 --> 03:33.347
Okay. Got to jet. Um...

03:33.381 --> 03:34.882
Ooh, thanks so much.

03:34.915 --> 03:36.484
Okay, good to see you guys!

03:36.517 --> 03:37.751
Bye, Josh! Bye!
Bye!

03:37.785 --> 03:38.686
Bye!
Bye!

03:38.719 --> 03:40.554
Okay, you have got
to get into that camp.

03:40.588 --> 03:42.923
This is your chance to go back
when you two fell in love.

03:42.956 --> 03:44.892
Okay. I'm gonna go see
the camp director.

03:44.925 --> 03:45.826
(squeals)

03:45.859 --> 03:48.262
I can't run in these.

03:48.296 --> 03:50.298
(chuckles)

03:54.702 --> 03:57.838
You're just so cute
for buying candy for the kids.

03:57.871 --> 03:59.807
Even though
you know

03:59.840 --> 04:03.544
giving kids sweets
is like giving them cigarettes.

04:03.577 --> 04:04.812
Everybody loves candy.

04:04.845 --> 04:09.417
You're just so nice for doing
that camp program every year,

04:09.450 --> 04:12.052
passing up all those extra hours
at work

04:12.085 --> 04:14.788
that could get you promoted
to manager.

04:14.822 --> 04:16.890
You know, I don't mind.
I love those kids.

04:16.923 --> 04:20.293
Maybe because you're like
a big kid yourself.

04:20.327 --> 04:22.363
That's why you're so good
at talking to them.

04:22.396 --> 04:23.531
And one day,

04:23.564 --> 04:26.834
when we have kids and they say,
"Why don't we have shoes?"

04:26.867 --> 04:31.071
you can say, "So that other kids
can have candy."

04:31.104 --> 04:35.075
Um, V, sometimes it's like...
(scoffs)

04:35.108 --> 04:37.811
like you don't understand me
or...

04:37.845 --> 04:39.747
even believe in me.

04:39.780 --> 04:41.014
It sucks.

04:41.048 --> 04:44.585
What? Of course I do.
I believe that

04:44.618 --> 04:45.686
one day you will focus

04:45.719 --> 04:49.657
on our future
instead of fun stuff.

04:49.690 --> 04:51.692
Mmm.

04:52.860 --> 04:53.827
Your little nose.

04:53.861 --> 04:55.863
(squeaks)

04:58.466 --> 04:59.800
So, Josh said
you wanted to help.

04:59.833 --> 05:01.469
We would love for you to get
involved.

05:01.502 --> 05:02.436
You know, people think

05:02.470 --> 05:05.639
of West Covina
as this prosperous suburb...

05:05.673 --> 05:07.641
But ten percent of its residents
live below the poverty line.

05:07.675 --> 05:09.377
I know.
And I am willing to help.

05:09.410 --> 05:11.445
I've cleared my schedule.
So, here are my ideas.

05:11.479 --> 05:13.981
I can host a really good
game of tug-of-war,

05:14.014 --> 05:16.350
I know a great recipe
for organic bug juice,

05:16.384 --> 05:18.652
and don't even get me
started on my lanyard skills.

05:18.686 --> 05:20.788
Okay, we don't need
any more counselors.

05:20.821 --> 05:21.822
We're covered there.

05:21.855 --> 05:24.024
Okay. Forget the bug juice.

05:24.057 --> 05:25.493
Here's what I can offer:

05:25.526 --> 05:27.495
a female empowerment program.
Hear me out.

05:27.528 --> 05:30.398
I did it at my old high school
in Scarsdale. Huge success.

05:30.431 --> 05:32.633
All the girls ended up
on the Pill because of me.

05:32.666 --> 05:36.370
Listen, Rebecca,
when we say, "Get involved,"

05:36.404 --> 05:38.906
what we mean is,
"Give us money."

05:38.939 --> 05:40.541
Our lawyers wouldn't let us
put, "Just give us

05:40.574 --> 05:42.410
some damn money" on the posters.

05:42.443 --> 05:44.912
Well, great. Okay, so if I give
you money, I can come to camp?

05:44.945 --> 05:47.515
No, no. Donors don't come
to the camp, Ms. Bunch,

05:47.548 --> 05:48.782
no matter how much money
they give.

05:49.683 --> 05:51.652
Here you go.

05:52.953 --> 05:54.855
This'll do.

05:54.888 --> 05:57.057
(laughs)
Welcome aboard.

05:57.090 --> 06:00.528
You are the new Director
of Female Empowerment.

06:00.561 --> 06:01.695
Yes! (chuckles)

06:03.096 --> 06:06.467
(horn honking)

06:08.569 --> 06:10.838
(chuckles)

06:10.871 --> 06:13.807
(both sigh)

06:13.841 --> 06:16.410
I was thinking about seeing a
movie tonight. You want to go?

06:16.444 --> 06:17.811
Oh, never mind.

06:17.845 --> 06:18.946
I forgot you
and your friends
Mmm...

06:18.979 --> 06:20.981
ironically watch Empire.

06:21.014 --> 06:23.551
Yeah, it's not ironic
for me anymore.

06:23.584 --> 06:25.686
Taraji's my everything.

06:25.719 --> 06:27.588
(chuckles)
But I can blow it off.

06:27.621 --> 06:29.857
No. I don't want you to do that.

06:29.890 --> 06:32.426
Why not? I like you.

06:32.460 --> 06:34.728
(commentator speaking
indistinctly on TV)

06:34.762 --> 06:37.731
I like you a lot, Greg.

06:37.765 --> 06:39.567
(chuckles, mutters)

06:39.600 --> 06:41.569
"I like you a lot, Greg."

06:41.602 --> 06:44.004
That's-that's funny.

06:44.037 --> 06:47.741
Yeah, no,
I'm, like, excited about this.

06:47.775 --> 06:50.143
I have butterflies.

06:50.177 --> 06:51.712
You can't tell?

06:51.745 --> 06:53.714
It's subtle.

06:53.747 --> 06:55.148
I'm serious.

06:55.182 --> 06:57.851
We've been hooking up for
a few weeks, and I'm into it.

06:57.885 --> 07:00.187
I'm not seeing
other guys anymore.

07:02.490 --> 07:04.458
What?

07:04.492 --> 07:05.726
So obviously

07:05.759 --> 07:07.461
I told her we needed some space.

07:07.495 --> 07:09.229
Because not seeing other people

07:09.262 --> 07:11.832
is like an inch away
from hiring a wedding band.

07:11.865 --> 07:13.867
It's better this way.
We have too many differences.

07:13.901 --> 07:15.002
She likes Chuck Palahniuk,

07:15.035 --> 07:16.504
and I think it's pretty obvious

07:16.537 --> 07:18.171
after Fight Club,
he's a one-trick pony.

07:18.205 --> 07:19.740
Dude.
What?

07:19.773 --> 07:20.874
I've been watching
 The View lately,

07:20.908 --> 07:22.610
and you're a commitment-phobe.

07:22.643 --> 07:24.678
(chuckles)
I am not.

07:24.712 --> 07:25.813
You're, like,
making up problems

07:25.846 --> 07:26.914
as an excuse
to break up with her.

07:26.947 --> 07:29.082
I think your behavior
reflects a deep-seated fear

07:29.116 --> 07:31.084
that if you love somebody,
she'll leave you.

07:31.118 --> 07:33.854
It's probably rooted in
your childhood trauma.

07:33.887 --> 07:37.190
Stop-stop
with your armchair psychology.

07:37.224 --> 07:38.626
I appreciated that insight.

07:38.659 --> 07:40.093
You're the only
one who gets me.

07:40.127 --> 07:41.762
We're just not compatible.

07:41.795 --> 07:43.497
If the perfect girl walked in
right now

07:43.531 --> 07:45.899
and said, "Greg, I like you,"

07:45.933 --> 07:49.903
I would be into it. Totally.

07:49.937 --> 07:52.005
Hey! My beach buds!
Hey! Oh.

07:52.039 --> 07:53.841
Yeah.

07:53.874 --> 07:55.843
What's up? Oh, you must be
the dude that overslept.

07:55.876 --> 07:56.910
Hector.
Hector.

07:56.944 --> 07:58.512
So, uh,

07:58.546 --> 07:59.647
what's up with you?
You know,

07:59.680 --> 08:01.649
my, uh, ex-wife,
she took Madison

08:01.682 --> 08:05.653
for the weekend, and I have
just been stone-cold chillin'.

08:05.686 --> 08:06.820
(crying):
I know.

08:06.854 --> 08:10.190
I miss her, too,
Snail-iana Grande.

08:10.223 --> 08:12.059
How about you cats?
What have you guys been up to?

08:12.092 --> 08:14.061
You know, we were just
talking about trying

08:14.094 --> 08:15.696
to watch this fight,
but it's, uh, Pay-per-view,

08:15.729 --> 08:16.697
so it's a little expensive.

08:16.730 --> 08:17.698
The one you mean with the,

08:17.731 --> 08:19.700
the two guys that are
like this on the poster?

08:19.733 --> 08:20.568
That's the one.

08:20.601 --> 08:22.002
Yep.
Oh!

08:22.035 --> 08:23.070
Well, I was totally
planning on watching that.

08:23.103 --> 08:23.837
Yeah?

08:23.871 --> 08:24.905
You know what?

08:24.938 --> 08:26.039
Why don't you guys come over

08:26.073 --> 08:27.074
and we can all
watch it together?

08:27.107 --> 08:27.808
HECTOR:
Wha--?

08:27.841 --> 08:29.710
That would be awesome actually.

08:29.743 --> 08:31.278
I'm in. I don't have any plans
this weekend anymore.

08:31.311 --> 08:33.714
Free man.
No one tying me down.

08:33.746 --> 08:36.082
(laughs):
Oh, this is great then!

08:36.116 --> 08:37.317
This is awesome!

08:37.350 --> 08:39.787
And we'll have ourselves
a little party, you dig?

08:39.820 --> 08:41.722
I dig.
All right!
I-I also dig.

08:41.755 --> 08:43.890
You know, here's
a little known fact.

08:43.924 --> 08:47.094
I used to be the social director
of my frat back in college.
No.

08:47.127 --> 08:47.961
Yeah.
No way.

08:47.995 --> 08:49.863
They used to call me
king of the spread.

08:49.897 --> 08:52.566
Oh, nice, 'cause you had
your way with the ladies?

08:52.600 --> 08:54.668
No, it was because I make pâté.

08:54.702 --> 08:56.069
It's all in the onions.

08:56.103 --> 08:58.238
You have to caramelize
for, like, 18 hours.

08:58.271 --> 09:00.574
Which if I leave right now,

09:00.608 --> 09:03.911
I will have everything
ready to spready.

09:03.944 --> 09:05.679
Spready, all right.
Spready.

09:05.713 --> 09:07.748
I'll bring some crackers.
Oh, that'd be great, great.

09:07.781 --> 09:09.717
Um, lend an ear.

09:09.750 --> 09:10.651
Yeah.
Um,

09:10.684 --> 09:11.852
the, uh, fight?

09:11.885 --> 09:13.353
That's boxing, right?

09:13.386 --> 09:15.589
(bell dings)

09:15.623 --> 09:16.890
Okay, feeling good?
Feeling loose?

09:16.924 --> 09:18.158
Yeah.
Feeling cute?
Feeling 16?

09:18.191 --> 09:19.593
Yeah.
All right, get your
head in the game.

09:19.627 --> 09:20.327
Okay.

09:20.360 --> 09:22.329
Spit.

09:22.362 --> 09:23.764
Cut me.
Okay.

09:24.798 --> 09:25.866
All right.

09:25.899 --> 09:27.968
Inventory.

09:28.001 --> 09:31.204
Handi Wipes, trail mix,
flashlight, bug spray--

09:31.238 --> 09:32.873
Oh, some extra toilet paper.

09:32.906 --> 09:34.141
Heaven forbid you
have to use leaves.

09:34.174 --> 09:35.308
Oh, I got a rash one time.

09:35.342 --> 09:36.610
It almost made me infertile.

09:36.644 --> 09:39.012
Unfortunately, it did not.

09:39.046 --> 09:40.614
Do you need anything else?

09:40.648 --> 09:41.514
I don't think so, no.
Okay.

09:41.548 --> 09:43.250
Oh, there's one thing
I have to show you.

09:43.283 --> 09:44.718
So this is a letter

09:44.752 --> 09:46.654
that I wrote to Josh
our last day of camp.

09:46.687 --> 09:48.055
I was gonna give it
to him and then he...

09:48.088 --> 09:49.189
you know,
he broke up with me.

09:49.222 --> 09:50.624
So I was gonna mail it to him,
then I decided not to.

09:50.658 --> 09:51.692
So I decided to burn it,

09:51.725 --> 09:52.826
but then I didn't
do that, either.

09:52.860 --> 09:53.927
That's why it's
a little scorched.

09:53.961 --> 09:55.295
Anyway, I want to get him alone

09:55.328 --> 09:57.064
and read him this letter.

09:57.097 --> 09:58.732
And I think if I do,

09:58.766 --> 10:00.934
all of his feelings from when
we were together at camp--

10:00.968 --> 10:02.335
you know, falling in love
under the stars--

10:02.369 --> 10:03.671
it-it'll come back to him.

10:03.704 --> 10:04.872
Tell me what you think.

10:04.905 --> 10:08.909
* Dear Joshua Felix Chan

10:08.942 --> 10:13.146
* I remember the moment
it beg-- *

10:13.180 --> 10:14.247
Yeah, no.
Uh-uh.

10:14.281 --> 10:15.082
No, no, no.
What?

10:15.115 --> 10:16.149
Don't do this.

10:16.183 --> 10:17.284
This is dumb.

10:17.317 --> 10:18.852
You're a grown-ass lady.

10:18.886 --> 10:20.353
You don't need cutesy letters
from childhood.

10:20.387 --> 10:22.022
You just need to use
what God gave you.

10:22.055 --> 10:24.024
My charm and my wit?

10:24.057 --> 10:25.926
It's a weird name
for your boobs.

10:25.959 --> 10:27.728
Actually, my boobs names
are Bonnie and Clyde.

10:27.761 --> 10:29.663
And my ovaries
are Hustle and Flow.

10:29.697 --> 10:30.798
Oh, oh, oh!

10:30.831 --> 10:31.965
That is nice!

10:31.999 --> 10:33.133
Yeah, yeah, I know.
All right.

10:33.166 --> 10:34.401
Forget the letter.

10:34.434 --> 10:35.435
Okay.
All right?

10:35.468 --> 10:38.338
And just go...

10:38.371 --> 10:40.240
get him, kiddo. Boop.
Okay.

10:40.273 --> 10:42.910
Josh, Josh! Hey, hey, Josh!

10:42.943 --> 10:44.077
Hey! It's so cool
that you're here.

10:44.111 --> 10:45.178
